ឆ្នាំសិក្សា២០១៨-២០១៩។</p>\n\n<p><strong>ថ្ងៃទី០២-០៧ ធ្នូ ឆ្នាំ២០១៩</strong></p>\n\n<p>យុវសិស្ស ម៉ៅ សុវណ្ណាគង់ និងយុវសិស្ស នៅ រក្សាបុត្រ ថ្នាក់ទី១២ នៃសាលារៀន អន្តរទ្វីប អាមេរិកាំង សាខាទួលគោក បានចាប់ដៃសហការជាក្រុមជាមួយយុវសិស្ស ឆន ច័ន្ទតារាឈុនហួរ មកពីវិទ្យាល័យទួលទំពូង ទទួលបានរង្វាន់ Award Winner ក្នុងការប្រកួតខ្សែភាពយន្តកុមារអន្តរជាតិអាស៊ាន ឆ្នាំ២០១៩ (Asian International Children Film Festival 2019) របស់ JENESYS ក្រោមប្រធានបទ &laquo;ការបង្កបញ្ហាដល់អ្នកដទៃដើម្បីផលប្រយោជន៍ខ្លួនឯង&raquo; នៅក្នុងមហោស្រពទីក្រុងមិណាមិ អាវ៉ាជិ ខេត្តហ៊ីយ៉ូហ្គោ នៅប្រទេសជប៉ុន</p>\n\n<p><strong>ថ្ងៃទី១៥ ខែធ្នូ ឆ្នាំ២០១៩</strong></p>\n\n<p>កុមារី សម្បត្តិ សិរីកា ថ្នាក់ទី៦ក ឈ្នះមេដាយមាសពីការប្រកួតគណិតវិទ្យាអន្តរជាតិនៅកម្ពុជា និងឈ្នះមេដាយសំរឹទ្ធិពីការប្រកួតគណិតវិទ្យាអូឡាំពិកអន្តរជាតិនៅប្រទេសថៃ និងកុមារី សម្បត្តិ សិរីសោភា ថ្នាក់ទី៣ក ឈ្នះមេដាយប្រាក់ពីការប្រកួតគណិតវិទ្យាអន្តរជាតិនៅកម្ពុជា និងឈ្នះមេដាយមាសពីការប្រកួតគណិតវិទ្យាអូឡាំពិកអន្តរជាតិនៅប្រទេសថៃ</p>\n\n<p><strong>ថ្ងៃទី២៧-២៩ ខែធ្នូ ឆ្នាំ២០១៩</strong></p>\n\n<p>កីឡាការីនី លី អ៊ីហ័រ ថ្នាក់ទី១២ង កីឡាការីនី លី មុនីនាថ ថ្នាក់ទី១១ង និងកីឡាការីនី ស្រ៊ុនស្រ៊ន ស៊ីម៉ូណា ថ្នាក់ទី៨ឃ ទទទួលបានមេដាយសំរឹទ្ធិលើការប្រកួតទ្វារគុនព្រលឹងល្បុក្កតោជាក្រុមផ្នែកនារី ក្នុងការប្រកួតក្បាច់គុនល្បុក្កតោជ្រើសរើសជើងឯកថ្នាក់ជាតិឆ្នាំ២០១៩ នៅមជ្ឈមណ្ឌលការ៉ាតេដូ នៃសាកលវិទ្យាល័យភូមិន្ទភ្នំពេញ ដែលរៀបចំដោយសហព័ន្ធកីឡាគុនល្បុក្កតោកម្ពុជា សហការជាមួយក្រសួងអប់រំ យុវជន និងកីឡា។</p>', '<p><strong>December 02-07, 2019</strong></p>\n\n<p>Mr. Mao Sovannakong and Mr. Reaksabotr Neou, grade 12 students from American Intercon School, Toul Kork campus, have teamed up with Mr. Chandara Chunhour Chhorn, from Tuol Tumpoung High School and received the Award Winner at the Asian International Children Film Festival 2019, under the theme of &ldquo;How do you think about causing others trouble. Is it okay if only you are good? Can you think about other people?&rdquo; in Minami-Awaji City, Hyogo Prefecture, Japan.</p>\n\n<p><strong>December 15, 2019</strong></p>\n\n<p>Miss Sambath Serika, from grade 6A, won gold medal in International Math competition, Cambodia and won bronze medal in International Math Olympiad, Thailand. Sambath Sereisophia, from grade 3A, won silver medal in International Math competition, Cambodia and won gold medal in International Olympiad, Thailand.</p>\n\n<p><strong>December 27-29, 2019</strong></p>\n\n<p>Miss Lee Ehor, Grade 12E, Miss Ly Monineath, Grade 12E, and Miss Srunsrorn Simona, Grade 8D, won bronze medal in women group Tvea Kun Prolueng Lbokator at National Lbokator Martial Art Competition 2019 held in Karate Center, Royal University of Phnom Penh, organized by Cambodia Lbokator Federation cooperated with Ministry of Education, Youth and Sport.</p>\n\n<p><strong>February 14, 2020</strong></p>\n\n<p>Mr. Thouk Soksambath, from grade 6B, won 2nd place in long jump at Phnom Penh Capital Primary School Athletes 2019-2020 event organized by Department of Education, Youth and Sports of Phnom Penh held at Chea Sim Boeung Keng Kong High School.</p>\n\n<p><strong>February 19, 2020</strong></p>\n\n<p>Mr. Phan Uddampanchakrith, former grade 12B in academic year 2017-2018 at TK Campus of American Intercon School, passed the aviation test and has become a pilot in Quezon City, Philippine.</p>\n\n<p><strong>February 20-21, 2020</strong></p>\n\n<p>Mr. Chhay Kimsenh, from grade 12B at MTT Campus, won 3rd place in Phnom Penh Outstanding Student examination at Indratevy exam center (Indratevy High School).</p>\n\n<p><strong>February 28, 2020</strong></p>\n\n<p>Mr. Taing Kimgech won 2nd place in 100-meter sprint at Phnom Penh Secondary School Athletes competition 2019-2020 organized by Department of Education, Youth and Sports of Phnom Penh at Olympic Stadium.</p>\n\n<p><strong>March 07, 2020</strong></p>\n\n<p>4 students were awarded in drawing competition under a theme: &ldquo;New Perception toward the World&rdquo; at the International Secondary School Arts Festival 2020, national level, held at University of Cambodia; and they won the 1st place and were selected as the best artist in Kingdom of Cambodia to attend the exhibition in Japan on August 05, 2020:</p>\n\n<table class=\"table table-bordered\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<th>No</th>\n			<th>ID</th>\n			<th>Student Name</th>\n			<th>Sex</th>\n			<th>Grade</th>\n			<th>Campus</th>\n			<th>Rank</th>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>1</td>\n			<td>m4926</td>\n			<td>Lay Youmeasmanith</td>\n			<td>F</td>\n			<td>11D</td>\n			<td>MTT</td>\n			<td>1</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>2</td>\n			<td>m6073</td>\n			<td>Lav Rithysak</td>\n			<td>M</td>\n			<td>9C</td>\n			<td>MTT</td>\n			<td>2</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>3</td>\n			<td>m6849</td>\n			<td>Ly Monirachana</td>\n			<td>F</td>\n			<td>9A</td>\n			<td>MTT</td>\n			<td>3</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>4</td>\n			<td>m6650</td>\n			<td>Ung Thavrin</td>\n			<td>M</td>\n			<td>8A</td>\n			<td>MTT</td>\n			<td>4</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p><strong>June 22-27, 2020</strong></p>\n\n<p>3 primary students won the award in the Think! Think! World Cup! Online competition organized by Think Think:</p>\n\n<table class=\"table table-bordered\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<th>No</th>\n			<th>ID</th>\n			<th>Student Name</th>\n			<th>Grade</th>\n			<th>Campus</th>\n			<th>Rank</th>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>1</td>\n			<td>b3666</td>\n			<td>Mr. Chea Sithireach</td>\n			<td>5D</td>\n			<td>MTT</td>\n			<td>1 over all candidates</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>2</td>\n			<td>b4545</td>\n			<td>Mr. Hing Ngetvirayuth</td>\n			<td>3A</td>\n			<td>MTT</td>\n			<td>2 for 3<sup>rd</sup>&nbsp;grade</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>3</td>\n			<td>CCb0081</td>\n			<td>Mr. Chea Kimhok</td>\n			<td>2A</td>\n			<td>CC</td>\n			<td>3 for 2<sup>nd</sup>&nbsp;grade</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p><strong>July 20, 2020</strong></p>\n\n<p>American Intercon School was officially recognized by Ministry of Education, Youth, and Sport for online teaching and learning.</p>\n\n<p><strong>August 2020</strong></p>\n\n<p>6 students received bachelor de